 anticipated. The revised standard time for the first 460 units was calculated based on this learning rate.\"", "\"LABOUR EFFICIENCY VARIANCES\":Labour efficiency variances are calculated to measure the difference between the standard hours for actual production and the actual hours worked, adjusted for the learning rate. These variances help in evaluating the efficiency of labor usage in production. In Bokco's case, variances were calculated based on both 90% and 85% learning rates.", "\"END OF LEARNING PERIOD\":", "\"LABOUR EFFICIENCY PLANNING VARIANCE\":\"Labour efficiency planning variance\" arises when the standard hours need to be revised due to factors beyond the control of operational managers, such as changes in employment legislation, customer demands for higher quality, or incorrect estimates of the learning effect. It is calculated as the difference between the standard hours for actual production and the revised hours for actual production, multiplied by the standard rate.", "\"LABOUR EFFICIENCY OPERATIONAL VARIANCE\":\"Labour efficiency operational variance is calculated as (Revised hours for actual production - actual hours for actual production) * standard rate.\"", "\"PLANNING VARIANCES\":\"Planning variances reflect factors outside of the control of operational managers and are calculated using the original standard.\"", "\"EVALUATING MANAGER PERFORMANCE AND CALCULATING VARIANCES FOR CHAFF CO\":\"Chaff Co processes and sells brown rice, using a standard costing system to monitor performance. The case involves evaluating manager performance based on variances calculated for month 1, including material price, material usage, labour rate, labour efficiency, variable overhead expenditure, and variable overhead efficiency variances.\"", "\"VARIABLE OVERHEAD EXPENDITURE VARIANCE\":\"Variable overhead expenditure variance is the difference between the actual variable overhead costs incurred and the standard variable overhead costs expected to be incurred, based on actual hours worked.\"", "\"STANDARD CONTRIBUTION PER TONNE\":\"Standard contribution per tonne = Standard selling price - Standard variable costs\"", "\"BUDGETED PRODUCTION AND SALES\":\"Budgeted production and sales refer to the planned quantity of production and sales for a specific period.\"", "\"ACTUAL PRODUCTION AND SALES\":\"Actual production and sales refer to the actual quantity of production and sales achieved during a specific period.\"", "\"PURCHASING MANAGER PERFORMANCE\":\"The performance of the purchasing manager is evaluated based on variances such as material price variance and material usage variance, and their impact on overall costs and quality.\"", "\"PRODUCTION DIRECTOR PERFORMANCE\":\"The performance of the production director is evaluated based on variances such as labour rate variance and labour efficiency variance, and their impact on productivity and morale.\"", "\"MAINTENANCE MANAGER PERFORMANCE\":\"The performance of the maintenance manager is evaluated based on variances such as fixed overhead expenditure variance and the impact of maintenance decisions on production and costs.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}